philipm.cs5.software.development.user.system

Class InputPackages

  • java.lang.Object
    • philipm.cs5.software.development.user.system.InputPackages
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class InputPackages
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is used to create a package to send to the server. It creates an object which essentially stores an array. Element 0 of this array is a command which indicates what the server has to do. The command is a constant and stored in this class.
    Author:
    mortimer
    See Also:
